Westchester, Florida

Westchester is a [census-designated place](/Census-designated_place) (CDP) and a neighborhood nestled within the sprawling expanse of [Miami-Dade County, Florida](/Miami-Dade_County,_Florida). It’s a place that exists, breathing the humid air of the [Miami metropolitan area](/Miami_metropolitan_area) in the southern reaches of [South Florida](/South_Florida). Prior to the [2020 U.S. census](/2020_United_States_census), a significant geographical and demographic shift occurred when the adjacent [University Park CDP](/University_Park,_Florida) was absorbed into Westchester, effectively doubling its footprint and its populace. According to the most recent census data from 2020, the combined entity of Westchester is home to 56,384 souls.

### Geography

Westchester occupies a strategic position, situated approximately 10 miles (16 km) to the west of the bustling heart of [downtown Miami](/Downtown_Miami). Its geographical coordinates are 25°44′49″N 80°20′13″W, placing it firmly within the temporal rhythm of the [United States](/United_States). The land here rests at an elevation of about 8 feet (2.4 m) above sea level, a fact that probably doesn’t register unless a hurricane decides to remind everyone of their proximity to the coast.

The boundaries of Westchester are clearly defined, though perhaps not always intuitively. To its north lie the communities of [Sweetwater](/Sweetwater,_Miami-Dade_County,_Florida) and [Fontainebleau](/Fontainebleau,_Florida). To the east, it shares a border with [Coral Terrace](/Coral_Terrace,_Florida). The southern edge of Westchester abuts against [Olympia Heights](/Olympia_Heights,_Florida) and [Westwood Lakes](/Westwood_Lakes,_Florida). And to the west, it meets [Tamiami](/Tamiami,_Florida). It's worth noting that the former [University Park CDP](/University_Park,_Florida), now an integral part of Westchester, encompasses the western half of this expanded territory. The sprawling campus of [Florida International University](/Florida_International_University) is a prominent feature within the northwestern quadrant of the CDP.

According to the meticulous records of the [United States Census Bureau](/United_States_Census_Bureau), the Westchester CDP, in its current configuration, sprawls across a total area of 8.11 square miles (21.0 km²). Of this considerable expanse, a mere 0.15 square miles (0.39 km²), representing a modest 1.89%, is accounted for by water. The rest is, presumably, land.

### Demographics

The historical population figures for Westchester paint a picture of steady, if sometimes modest, growth, punctuated by a rather dramatic surge in the most recent census.

